{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Client Handover",
  "description": "Generate professional client-facing IPA documentation using section-segmented architecture with specialized subagents (batched parallel execution). CRITICAL: Subagents extract REAL data from source files (ANA-050 spec for business requirements, LPD Start node for configuration variables, LPD activities for workflow). Template handles both old and new workflow formats. Subagents save files directly using fsWrite. Creates comprehensive Excel report with workflow diagrams, business requirements, activity guides, and maintenance instructions. NO code criticism - focuses on how to understand and maintain the IPAs. Scalable to any IPA size. Production-grade: 95% ready (extracts truth, not AI-generated content).",
  "version": 38,
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "newSession": true,
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "IMPORTANT: This is a HOOK-TRIGGERED workflow, NOT a spec creation request. Do NOT route this through spec creation. Do NOT ask about feature vs bugfix. Do NOT ask about requirements vs design. Execute the workflow below DIRECTLY by starting with Step 1 (user selection).\n\nIPA Client Handover Documentation - Section-Segmented Architecture\n\nThis is CLIENT-FACING documentation, NOT an internal code review.\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nARCHITECTURE: Section-Segmented Documentation\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nSolution: Multi-pass documentation generation\n- Python extracts and organizes data by documentation sections (5 sections)\n- AI analyzes each section with specialized subagents (parallel)\n- Python merges results into master documentation\n- ONE Excel report generated\n\nSections:\n1. Business Requirements - What and why (from functional spec)\n2. Workflow - How it flows (from LPD activities)\n3. Configuration - What can be changed (from config variables)\n4. Activity Guide - Reference documentation (from activities)\n5. Validation - Production proof (from WU logs)\n\nPython Role: Extract, organize, merge, format\nAI Role: Analyze sections, create client-friendly documentation\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nWORKFLOW - FOLLOW EXACTLY\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nSTEP 0: CLEAN TEMP FOLDER (AUTOMATIC - NO USER PROMPT)\n\nExecute PowerShell command to wipe Temp folder:\nRemove-Item Temp/* -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n\nThis ensures clean slate and prevents IDE indexing issues from accumulated files.\n\n\n\nMonitor workspace size:\n$tempFiles = (Get-ChildItem Temp -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object).Count\n$tempSize = [math]::Round((Get-ChildItem Temp -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object -Property Length -Sum).Sum / 1MB, 2)\n\nShow: \"📊 Workspace Status: Temp has $tempFiles files ($tempSize MB)\"\n\nIf ($tempFiles -gt 50 -or $tempSize -gt 100) {\n    Show warning: \"⚠️ Temp folder is large despite cleanup.\"\n}\n\nSTEP 1-5: USER SELECTION (Interactive)\n   1. List clients in Projects/ → User selects\n   2. List RICE items → User selects\n   3. List *.lpd files → User selects ONE\n   4. Check for *.docx (spec) and *_log.txt (WU log)\n   5. Confirm selection → User confirms\n\nSTEP 6: EXTRACT DATA (Python)\n   \n   # Extract LPD data\n   executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_lpd_data import extract_lpd_data; extract_lpd_data(['<lpd_path>'], 'Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json')\\\"\")\n   \n   # Extract spec data (if available)\n   If spec file exists:\n       executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_spec import extract_spec; extract_spec('<spec_path>', 'Temp/<ProcessName>_spec_data.json')\\\"\")\n   \n   # Extract WU log data (if available)\n   If WU log exists:\n       executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_wu_log import extract_wu_log; extract_wu_log('<wu_log_path>', 'Temp/<ProcessName>_wu_data.json')\\\"\")\n   \n   Verify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json\")\n\nSTEP 7: ORGANIZE BY SECTIONS (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_ClientHandover/organize_by_sections.py Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json <spec_json_or_none> <wu_json_or_none> Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n   \n   Creates 5 section files:\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_section_business.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_section_workflow.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_section_configuration.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_section_activities.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_section_validation.json\n\nSTEP 8: LAUNCH SECTION ANALYZERS (Batched Parallel Execution)\n   \n   BATCH 1: Launch business requirements and workflow analyzers (2 subagents)\n   \n   Show: \"→ Batch 1/2: Launching business requirements and workflow analyzers...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-business-requirements-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Read spec data and section data\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_spec_data.json')\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_section_business.json')\n\nSTEP 2: Extract business requirements from ANA-050 spec\nUse spec sections (Overview, Requirements Details, Proposed Solution, Field Mapping) to create requirements.\nExtract stakeholders from spec reviewers/approvers.\nDefine scope from spec content.\n\nSTEP 3: Save analysis using chunked writes if large:\n\nIf output > 1000 lines: Use fsWrite for first 500 lines, then fsAppend for remaining chunks.\nOtherwise: Use fsWrite normally.\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_business.json' using fsWrite().\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing business requirements in batch 1\"\n   )\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-workflow-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Read section data\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_section_workflow.json')\n\nSTEP 2: Map process workflow and approval paths\nCreate workflow_steps, approval_paths, and decision_points.\n\nSTEP 3: Save analysis using chunked writes if large:\n\nIf output > 1000 lines: Use fsWrite for first 500 lines, then fsAppend for remaining chunks.\nOtherwise: Use fsWrite normally.\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_workflow.json' using fsWrite().\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing workflow in batch 1\"\n   )\n   \n   Wait for Batch 1 to complete before proceeding.\n   Show: \"✓ Batch 1/2 complete: Business requirements and workflow analyzed\"\n   \n   BATCH 2: Launch configuration, activities, and validation analyzers (3 subagents)\n   \n   Show: \"→ Batch 2/2: Launching configuration, activities, and validation analyzers...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-configuration-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Read LPD data and section data\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json')\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_section_configuration.json')\n\nSTEP 2: Extract ACTUAL variables from Start node\nNavigate to processes[0]['activities'], find Start node, extract properties.\nCategorize: System Configuration (_configuration.*), File Channel (FileChannel*), Process Variables (others).\nDocument each with name, type, location, description, current value, how to modify.\n\nSTEP 3: Save analysis using chunked writes if large:\n\nIf output > 1000 lines: Use fsWrite for first 500 lines, then fsAppend for remaining chunks.\nOtherwise: Use fsWrite normally.\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_configuration.json' using fsWrite().\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing configuration in batch 2\"\n   )\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-activity-guide-generator\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Read section data\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_section_activities.json')\n\nSTEP 2: Create activity reference documentation in business terms\nCreate activities array and activity_groups.\n\nSTEP 3: Save analysis using chunked writes if large:\n\nIf output > 1000 lines: Use fsWrite for first 500 lines, then fsAppend for remaining chunks.\nOtherwise: Use fsWrite normally.\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_activities.json' using fsWrite().\",\n       explanation=\"Generating activity guide in batch 2\"\n   )\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-validation-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Read section data\nreadFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_section_validation.json')\n\nSTEP 2: Analyze work unit logs for production validation\nCreate test_summary, performance, and production_readiness.\n\nSTEP 3: Save analysis using chunked writes if large:\n\nIf output > 1000 lines: Use fsWrite for first 500 lines, then fsAppend for remaining chunks.\nOtherwise: Use fsWrite normally.\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_validation.json' using fsWrite().\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing validation data in batch 2\"\n   )\n   \n   Wait for Batch 2 to complete before proceeding.\n   Show: \"✓ Batch 2/2 complete: Configuration, activities, and validation analyzed\"\n   \n   IMPORTANT: Batched execution prevents resource exhaustion.\n   Each subagent saves its own output file directly using fsWrite().\n   Subagents load their own steering files as needed.\n\nSTEP 9: VERIFY SUBAGENT OUTPUTS\n   \n   Verify all files were saved by subagents:\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_business.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_workflow.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_configuration.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_activities.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_doc_validation.json\")\n\nSTEP 10: MERGE DOCUMENTATION (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_ClientHandover/merge_documentation.py Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n   \n   Creates: Temp/<ProcessName>_master_documentation.json\n\nSTEP 11: BUILD ipa_data FOR REPORT (AI)\n   \n   readFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_master_documentation.json')\n   \n   Build ipa_data dictionary from master documentation:\n   \n   ipa_data = {\n       'client_name': '<Client>',\n       'process_group': '<RICE>',\n       'processes': [{\n           'name': '<ProcessName>',\n           'file': '<ProcessName>.lpd',\n           'activity_count': <count>,\n           'activities': [...]\n       }],\n       'workflow_steps': master['workflow']['workflow_steps'],\n       'business_requirements': master['business_requirements'],\n       'production_validation': master['validation'],\n       'config_variables': master['configuration']['config_variables'],\n       'maintenance_guide': {\n           'configuration': master['configuration'],\n           'activity_guide': master['activity_guide']\n       }\n   }\n   \n   Show documentation summary in chat\n   Ask: \"Generate client handover report with this documentation?\"\n   WAIT for user confirmation\n\nSTEP 12: GENERATE REPORT (Python - Using Reusable Tool)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_ClientHandover/generate_client_handover_report.py <ProcessName> <Client> <RICE>\")\n   \n   This tool automatically:\n   - Loads all 5 subagent output files\n   - Verifies they exist\n   - Builds correct ipa_data structure\n   - Calls template with proper format\n   - Handles errors gracefully\n   \n   Verify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Client_Handover_Results/<Client>_<RICE>_*.xlsx\")\n\nSTEP 12.5: CLEANUP OLD RESULT FILES (Optional)\n   \n   Check result folder sizes:\n   $codingCount = (Get-ChildItem Coding_Standards_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count\n   $handoverCount = (Get-ChildItem Client_Handover_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count\n   $perfCount = (Get-ChildItem Performance_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count\n   $totalResults = $codingCount + $handoverCount + $perfCount\n   \n   If $totalResults > 20:\n       Show: \"📊 Result folders have $totalResults reports total\"\n       \n       userInput(\n           question=\"🧹 Archive old reports? (Moves reports older than 30 days to Archive/)\",\n           options=[\"Yes, archive old reports\", \"No, keep everything\"],\n           reason=\"general-question\"\n       )\n       \n       If user selects \"Yes, archive old reports\":\n           # Create Archive folders\n           executePwsh(\"New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path Archive/Coding_Standards, Archive/Client_Handover, Archive/Performance | Out-Null\")\n           \n           # Move old files (>30 days)\n           executePwsh(\"$oldFiles = Get-ChildItem Coding_Standards_Results, Client_Handover_Results, Performance_Results -File | Where-Object { $_.LastWriteTime -lt (Get-Date).AddDays(-30) }; $oldCount = ($oldFiles | Measure-Object).Count; foreach ($file in $oldFiles) { $dest = $file.DirectoryName -replace '_Results', ''; Move-Item $file.FullName -Destination \\\"Archive/$dest/\\\" -Force }; Write-Output \\\"✓ Archived $oldCount old reports\\\"\"\n           \n           # Show current counts\n           executePwsh(\"$currentCount = (Get-ChildItem Coding_Standards_Results, Client_Handover_Results, Performance_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count; Write-Output \\\"✓ $currentCount recent reports remain\\\"\")\n\nSTEP 12.6: CLEANUP OLD TEMP FILES (Optional)\n   \n   Check Temp folder size:\n   $tempCount = (Get-ChildItem Temp -File | Measure-Object).Count\n   \n   If $tempCount > 10:\n       Show: \"📊 Temp folder has $tempCount files\"\n       \n       userInput(\n           question=\"🧹 Clean up old Temp files? (Keeps current session data safe)\",\n           options=[\"Yes, clean old files\", \"No, keep everything\"],\n           reason=\"general-question\"\n       )\n       \n       If user selects \"Yes, clean old files\":\n           # Get files older than 5 minutes (not from current session)\n           executePwsh(\"$oldFiles = Get-ChildItem Temp -File | Where-Object { $_.LastWriteTime -lt (Get-Date).AddMinutes(-5) }; $oldCount = ($oldFiles | Measure-Object).Count; $oldFiles | Remove-Item -Force; Write-Output \\\"✓ Cleaned $oldCount old files\\\"\")\n           \n           # Show what was kept\n           executePwsh(\"$currentCount = (Get-ChildItem Temp -File | Measure-Object).Count; Write-Output \\\"✓ Kept $currentCount current session files\\\"\")\n\nSTEP 13: ASK ABOUT NEXT PROCESS\n   \n   If more LPD files in RICE item:\n   \n   Show summary:\n   ✓ Report generated: <filename>\n   ✓ Client-facing documentation complete\n   \n   Ask in plain text: \"Would you like to document another LPD file in this RICE item?\"\n   \n   If user says yes: Go to STEP 3 (list remaining files)\n   If user says no: Done\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nCRITICAL RULES\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n1. ONE PROCESS AT A TIME\n   - 1:1 mapping: ONE LPD → ONE report\n   - Do NOT combine multiple processes\n\n2. SECTION-SEGMENTED ANALYSIS WITH SUBAGENTS\n   - Launch 5 specialized subagents in 2 batches (Step 8)\n   - Batch 1: Business + Workflow (2 subagents)\n   - Batch 2: Configuration + Activities + Validation (3 subagents)\n   - Batched execution prevents resource exhaustion\n   - Subagents save files directly using fsWrite (Step 8)\n   - Subagents load their own steering files (no duplicate loading by main agent)\n\n3. CLIENT-FACING LANGUAGE ONLY\n   - NO code criticism or technical details\n   - Focus on WHAT and WHY, not HOW\n   - Use business language, not technical jargon\n   - Explain how to maintain, not how to fix\n\n4. PYTHON LIFTS HEAVY LOAD\n   - Python: Extract, organize, merge, format\n   - AI: Analyze sections, create documentation\n   - Python does NOT make judgments\n\n5. ONE EXCEL REPORT\n   - Multi-pass analysis → ONE master documentation file\n   - ONE Excel report per process\n   - 8+ sheets: Executive, Business, Validation, Config, Activities, Processes, Maintenance\n\n6. ERROR HANDLING\n   - If ANY step fails: STOP, show error, offer retry\n   - Verify files exist before proceeding (Test-Path)\n   - Show documentation summary BEFORE generating report\n\n7. GRACEFUL DEGRADATION\n   - If no spec: Infer requirements from LPD\n   - If no WU log: Note validation not available\n   - Report still generates with available data\n\nCONFIDENTIALITY: Client-facing documentation. Do not reference other clients.\n\nPERFORMANCE:\n- Extraction: ~1s per file\n- Organization: ~2s\n- AI analysis (5 subagents in parallel): ~30-60s\n- Report generation: <10s\n- Total: ~1-2 min per process\n\nSUBAGENTS:\n- ipa-business-requirements-analyzer: Business requirements from spec\n- ipa-workflow-analyzer: Process flow and approval paths\n- ipa-configuration-analyzer: Configuration guide with modification instructions\n- ipa-activity-guide-generator: Activity reference documentation\n- ipa-validation-analyzer: Production validation from WU logs\n\nAll subagents located in .kiro/agents/ with read and fsWrite tools. Subagents save files directly."
  }
}